text: Patrick J. Snyder (born October 10, 1956) is an American politician.https://docs.legis.wisconsin.gov/2017/legislators/assembly/1641 From Milwaukee, Wisconsin, Snyder went to University of Iowa. In 2000, Snyder worked for WSAU (AM). He then work for United States Representatives Sean Duffy as a field representative. He lived in Schofield, Wisconsin. In 2017, Snyder served in the Wisconsin State Assembly and is a Republican.WisconsinVote.org.-Patrick SnyderOurCampaigns.com.-Patrick Snyder ==Notes== Category:1956 births Category:Living people Category:People from Boone, Iowa Category:People from Schofield, Wisconsin Category:Politicians from Milwaukee Category:University of Iowa alumni Category:Wisconsin Republicans Category:Members of the Wisconsin State Assembly
